{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5e95397-0c60-4eb8-a461-0a9b783a9edf","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # verify SDK 11.0.100+ is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # confirm it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests\n```\n\nAlso update any NuGet package references (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions. Check the [.NET 11 release notes](https://github.com/dotnet/core/tree/main/release-notes/11.0) for breaking changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"823fb9a1-3583-4d87-b287-0ffae9d5ff5b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":343,"requestId":"400C:16BC0E:161A415:18F0A30:69F94B11"},"id":"f983ad75-97c8-4064-9b14-5f3342e891a6","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:42:49.126Z","parentId":"ed1063f5-ed77-458d-9ca0-bc950ca82daa"}
